returns.desc: Descriptor of the set at the specified revision

params.data: Hash of external content (e.g. metadata or schema)

returns.active: True if all sets have a revision > 0

setContract(uint64).notice: Returns the contract address associated with a set

setDescriptor(uint64,uint32).notice: Returns the descriptor at a given revision

setOwner(uint64).notice: Returns the current owner of a set

setRevision(uint64,uint32).notice: Resolves and validates a specific revision

setSnapshot(uint64,uint32).notice: Returns descriptor and elements of a set at a specific revision

setSota(uint64).notice: Returns the latest descriptor and current owner

setStatus(uint64[]).notice: Checks whether all provided set IDs are active

setTouch().notice: Touches a set (increments revision without any changes)

setUpdate(bytes32).notice: Updates the data hash of an existing set

setUpgrade(uint32,uint32).notice: Upgrades the kind or set revision
